quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,91,"No son (or offspring) did Allâh beget, nor is there any ilâh (god) along with Him. (If there had been many gods), then each god would have taken away what he had created, and some would have tried to overcome others! Glorified be Allâh above all that they attribute to Him!"
  23,92,"All-Knower of the unseen and the seen! Exalted be He over all that they associate as partners to Him!"
  23,93,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  25,37,"And Nûh’s (Noah) people, when they denied the Messengers, We drowned them, and We made them as a sign for mankind. And We have prepared a painful torment for the Zâlimûn (polytheists and wrong-doers)."
  25,38,"And (also) ‘Âd and Thamûd, and the Dwellers of Ar-Rass, and many generations in between."
  25,39,"And for each (of them) We put forward examples (as proofs and lessons), and each (of them) We brought to utter ruin (because of their disbelief and evil deeds)."
  26,10,"And (remember) when your Lord called Mûsâ (Moses) (saying): "
  26,11,""
  26,12,"He said: "